headline: 5 Revealing Analyst Questions From Vulcan Materials’s Q2 Earnings Call
summary: Vulcan Materials’ second quarter results came in below Wall Street’s expectations, as severe weather in key Southeastern markets weighed on shipment volumes and constrained revenue growth. Management cited record rainfall in states like Georgia and Tennessee as the primary challenge, which led to lower aggregate shipments despite stable operating margins. headline: VMC Q2 Deep Dive: Weather Disruptions and Infrastructure Tailwinds Shape Outlook
summary: Construction materials company Vulcan Materials (NYSE:VMC) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025 as sales rose 4.4% year on year to $2.10 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.45 per share was 2.8% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
